	        Send us your pictures   ·  Send us your stories A man was knocked down and killed by a minibus taxi in central Johannesburg on Tuesday morning, Gauteng paramedics said. The man, believed to be in his 30s, sustained serious head wounds. His body was found in the left-hand lane of Durban Street around 06:00, said ER24 spokesperson Russel Meiring. The taxi was parked a short distance away. Also read: 2 pupils among 4 pedestrians killed in KZN after taxi drives into them Meiring said the taxi driver escaped injury. Police were on the scene to investigate further. 24.com encourages commentary submitted via MyNews24. Contributions of 200 words or more will be considered for publication.  